		The Royal Canadian Mint is known throughout the world for its impeccable standards of quality and purity in all its products.  Because of its fine gold purity (.9999+), its flawless quality and its appealing design, the Canadian Gold Maple Leaf in particular, first minted in 1979, has become the preferred coin for many investors around the world today. The RCM’s insistence upon faultless planchets (the pure gold blanks from which coins are struck) has led to an enviable reputation among demanding investors and collectors.     Copyright 2002 A-Mark Precious Metals, Inc.
		







South African Krugerrand Coins
            Fineness = 0.916





















 


